<storybody><![CDATA[<p>Los Angeles, Jun 1 (PTI) Former "Glee" star Mark Salling has reportedly been axed from upcoming movie "Gods & Secrets" following his child porn indictment. </p><p>Director Adi Shankar insisted he would stand by the actor following his arrest in December until there was proof he had committed a crime, reported E!Online. </p><p>Shankar initially told, "Im going to wait for all the facts to arrive and if in fact these allegations are true, I will immediately take action, which includes removing his scenes from the project." </p><p>But now it seems the filmmaker has had enough of the drama surrounding Salling and sources said he is looking to reshoot the stars scenes with a replacement. </p><p>Shankar will personally fund the reshoots, according to reports - and he plans to donate a percentage of profits from the film, which also features Twilight stars Jackson Rathbone and Kellan Lutz, Denise Richards and "Breaking Bad" star R J Mitte, to an abused childrens charity. PTI NDS NDS</p>]]></storybody>
